{"title_page": "Malcolm Jellicoe", "text_new": "{{short description|Zimbabwean rugby union player}}\n{{ infobox rugby biography\n| image =\n| image_size =\n| caption =\n| birth_name = Malcolm Jellicoe\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1963|7|1}}\n| birth_place = [[Rhodesia]]\n| ru_position = [[Scrum-half (rugby union)|Scrum-half]]\n| height =  \n| weight =  \n| ru_amateuryears =  \n| ru_amateurclubs =  \n| ru_clubyears = 1987\n| ru_sevensnationalteam = \n| ru_sevensnationalyears =  \n| ru_clubcaps = \n| ru_clubpoints = \n| ru_nationalyears = 1987\n| ru_nationalteam = {{ru|Zimbabwe}} \n| ru_nationalcaps = 3\n| ru_nationalpoints = (0) \n}}\n\n'''Malcolm Jellicoe''' (born 1 July 1963<ref>[https://zimbabwe-today.com/malcolm-jellicoe-zimbabwe-rugby-union-player/ MALCOLM JELLICOE Zimbabwe rugby union player] Zimbabwe Today</ref>) is a Zimbabwean former rugby union player who played as scrum-half.\n\n==Career==\nJellicoe first played for [[Zimbabwe national rugby union team|Zimbabwe]] in the [[1987 Rugby World Cup]], which he captained, playing all the three pool stage matches, without scoring any try. He retired from the international career after the tournament.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{ESPNscrum|10209}}\n\n{{Zimbabwe Squad 1987 World Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jellicoe, Malcolm}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean rugby union players]]\n[[Category:Rugby union scrum-halves]]\n[[Category:White Zimbabwean sportspeople]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{ infobox rugby biography\n| image =\n| image_size =\n| caption =\n| birth_name = Malcolm Jellicoe\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1963|7|1}}\n| birth_place = [[Rhodesia]]\n| ru_position = [[Scrum-half (rugby union)|Scrum-half]]\n| height =  \n| weight =  \n| ru_amateuryears =  \n| ru_amateurclubs =  \n| ru_clubyears = 1987\n| ru_sevensnationalteam = \n| ru_sevensnationalyears =  \n| ru_clubcaps = \n| ru_clubpoints = \n| ru_nationalyears = 1987\n| ru_nationalteam