le10  = \n| demographics2_info10   =\n| blank_name_sec1        = {{PH wikidata|climate_title}}\n| blank_info_sec1        = {{PH wikidata|climate_type}}\n| blank1_name_sec1       = Native languages\n| blank1_info_sec1       = {{PH wikidata|language}}\n| blank2_name_sec1       = Sister localities\n| blank2_info_sec1       = \n| blank3_name_sec1       = \n| blank3_info_sec1       = \n| blank4_name_sec1       = \n| blank4_info_sec1       = \n| blank5_name_sec1       = \n| blank5_info_sec1       = \n| blank6_name_sec1       = \n| blank6_info_sec1       = \n| blank7_name_sec1       = \n| blank7_info_sec1       = \n| blank1_name_sec2       = Major religions\n| blank1_info_sec2       = \n| blank2_name_sec2       = Feast date\n| blank2_info_sec2       = \n| blank3_name_sec2       = Catholic diocese\n| blank3_info_sec2       =\n| blank4_name_sec2       = Patron saint \n| blank4_info_sec2       = \n| blank5_name_sec2       = \n| blank5_info_sec2       = \n| blank6_name_sec2       = \n| blank6_info_sec2       = \n| blank7_name_sec2       = \n| blank7_info_sec2       =\n| short_description      =\n| footnotes              =\n}}\n\n'''{{PH wikidata|name}}''', officially the '''{{PH wikidata|official_name}}''', ({{lang-ceb|Lungsod sa {{PH wikidata|name}}}}; {{lang-tgl|Bayan ng {{PH wikidata|name}}}}),  is a {{PH wikidata|income_class_ordinal}} [[{{PH wikidata|settlement_text}} of the Philippines|{{PH wikidata|settlement_text}}]] in the [[Philippine Province|province]] of {{PH wikidata|province}}, {{PH wikidata|country}}. According to the {{PH wikidata|population_as_of}}, it has a population of {{PH wikidata|population_total}} people.{{PH census|current}}\n\nIt is {{convert|93|km|sp=us|abbr=on|0}} South from [[Cebu City]]\n\nAlcoy is bordered to the north by the town of [[Dalaguete, Cebu|Dalaguete]], to the west is the town of [[Alegria, Cebu|Alegria]], to the east is the [[Cebu Strait]], and to the south is the town of [[Boljoon, Cebu|Boljoon]].\n\nIt is named after [[Alcoy, Spain|Alcoy]] in Spain.\n\n==Barangays==\n\nAlcoy comprises 8 barangays:\n{{PH brgy table lite|top}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202001| Atabay                         | 1754| 1535}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202002| Daan-Lungsod                   | 1863| 1569}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202003| Guiwang                        | 1564| 1490}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202004| Nug{{nbhyph}}as                | 3289| 2923}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202005| Pasol                          | 1789| 1740}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202006| Poblacion                      | 3610| 2991}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202007| [[Pugalo, Alcoy, Cebu|Pugalo]] | 2606| 2043}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202008| San Agustin                    |  504|  466}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|bottom|14757}}\n\n===Daan-Lungsod and Guiwang===\n\nDaan-Lungsod, formerly known as ''Mambahi''{{Citation needed|date=December 2008}}, is the southernmost barangay of Alcoy. [[Tingko Beach]] is located partly in this small barangay and partly in Guiwang. A fiesta is held in Daan-Lungsod every 3 May in honor of Santa Cruz. There is a reef called ''Mabad-on'' which appears during low tide, and is completely submerged during high tide. Mabad-on is listed as Mambahi Reef in the Philippine maritime and navigation map.{{Citation needed|date=December 2008}}\n\nThe elementary school is located in Guiwang. Guiwang celebrates 13 June the feast day of Saint Anthony of Padua.\n\nTwo ''baluwarti'' (watchtowers) still stand in the two barangays. The watchtowers are the oldest-surviving structures in Alcoy and they are reminders of the Spanish occupation of Cebu Island. They were used to warn the locals that [[Moro pirate|pirates]] were coming. Originally a settlement of Dalaguete, it was founded by the Spaniards in 1880 and was developed into a stop-over station for priests going to Dalaguete. In 1897, via a royal decree, ''Mambahi'' became a municipality and was renamed to Alcoy, after a city in Spain.<ref>https://www.beyondcebu.com/alcoy/</ref>\n\n===Poblacion===\n\nPoblacion is the principal barangay of Alcoy. It is where the main facilities of the town are located: the municipal government center, police station, and main health center.\n\n===Pugalo===\n\nThe country's largest [[Dolomite (mineral)|dolomite]] quarry is mined in [[Pugalo, Alcoy, Cebu|Pugalo]].\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Philippine Census|cols=2|align=center\n| source=[[Philippine Statistics Authority]]{{PH census|2015}}{{PH census|2010}}{{PH census|2007}}\n| name = Alcoy\n| 1903 =  6474\n| 1918 =  6575\n| 1939 =  6443\n| 1948 =  6708\n| 1960 =  7364\n| 1970 =  6965\n| 1975 =  8692\n| 1980 =  8129\n| 1990 = 10485\n| 1995 = 11539\n| 2000 = 13497\n| 2007 = 14571\n| 2010 = 14757\n| 2015 = 16979\n}}\n\n==Economy==\n\nAlcoy is mainly an agricultural town with Nug{{nbhyph}}as, a mountain barangay, more than half of commercial crops. The rest of the communities rely on subsistence fishing and backyard farming. The country's largest dolomite quarry is mined in [[Pugalo, Alcoy, Cebu|Pugalo]]. Beaches are located in Guiwang and Daanlungsod.\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Geographic location\n| Centre    = Alcoy\n| North     = [[Dalaguete, Cebu|Dalaguete]]\n| East      = ''[[Cebu Strait]]''\n| South     = [[Boljoon, Cebu|Boljoon]]\n| Southwest = [[Malabuyoc, Cebu|Malabuyoc]]\n| West      = [[Alegria, Cebu|Alegria]]\n| Northwest = [[Badian, Cebu|Badian]]\n| state     = off\n}}\n{{Cebu}}\n\n[[Category:Municipalities of Cebu]]\n", "text_old": "{{About||the mountain in Peru which is also spelled Alcay or Alcoy|Allqay}}\n{{short description|Municipality of the Philippines in the province of Cebu}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                   = {{PH wikidata|name}}\n| image_skyline          = {{PH wikidata|image_skyline}}\n| image_caption          = {{PH wikidata|image_caption}}\n| image_seal             =   \n| seal_size              = 100x80px\n| image_map              = {{PH wikidata|image_map}}\n| map_caption            = {{PH wikidata|map