 2019}}</ref>\n| demographics1_title3   = Revenue (\u20b1)\n| demographics1_info3    = {{PH wikidata|revenue}} {{PH wikidata|revenue_point_in_time}} \n| demographics1_title4   = Revenue Rank\n| demographics1_info4    = \n| demographics1_title5   = Assets (\u20b1)\n| demographics1_info5    = {{PH wikidata|assets}} {{PH wikidata|assets_point_in_time}} \n| demographics1_title6   = Assets Rank\n| demographics1_info6    = \n| demographics1_title7   = Liabilities (\u20b1)\n| demographics1_info7    = {{PH wikidata|liabilities}} {{PH wikidata|liabilities_point_in_time}} \n| demographics1_title8   = Liabilities Rank\n| demographics1_info8    = \n| demographics1_title9   = Expenditure (\u20b1)\n| demographics1_info9    = {{PH wikidata|expenditure}} {{PH wikidata|expenditure_point_in_time}} \n| demographics1_title10  = Expenditure Rank\n| demographics1_info10   = \n| demographics_type2     = \n| demographics2_title1   = Electricity\n| demographics2_info1    =  \n| demographics2_title2   = Water\n| demographics2_info2    =  \n| demographics2_title3   = Telecommunications\n| demographics2_info3    = \n| demographics2_title4   = Cable TV\n| demographics2_info4    =\n| demographics2_title5   = \n| demographics2_info5    =\n| demographics2_title6   = \n| demographics2_info6    =\n| demographics2_title7   = \n| demographics2_info7    =\n| demographics2_title8   = \n| demographics2_info8    =\n| demographics2_title9   = \n| demographics2_info9    =\n| demographics2_title10  = \n| demographics2_info10   =\n| blank_name_sec1        = {{PH wikidata|climate_title}}\n| blank_info_sec1        = {{PH wikidata|climate_type}}\n| blank1_name_sec1       = Native languages\n| blank1_info_sec1       = {{PH wikidata|language}}\n| blank2_name_sec1       = Sister localities\n| blank2_info_sec1       = \n| blank3_name_sec1       = \n| blank3_info_sec1       = \n| blank4_name_sec1       = \n| blank4_info_sec1       = \n| blank5_name_sec1       = \n| blank5_info_sec1       = \n| blank6_name_sec1       = \n| blank6_info_sec1       = \n| blank7_name_sec1       = \n| blank7_info_sec1       = \n| blank1_name_sec2       = Major religions\n| blank1_info_sec2       = \n| blank2_name_sec2       = Feast date\n| blank2_info_sec2       = \n| blank3_name_sec2       = Catholic diocese\n| blank3_info_sec2       =\n| blank4_name_sec2       = Patron saint \n| blank4_info_sec2       = \n| blank5_name_sec2       = \n| blank5_info_sec2       = \n| blank6_name_sec2       = \n| blank6_info_sec2       = \n| blank7_name_sec2       = \n| blank7_info_sec2       =\n| short_description      =\n| footnotes              =\n}}\n\n'''{{PH wikidata|name}}''', officially the '''{{PH wikidata|official_name}}''', ({{lang-ceb|Lungsod sa {{PH wikidata|name}}}}; {{lang-tgl|Bayan ng {{PH wikidata|name}}}}),  is a {{PH wikidata|income_class_ordinal}} [[{{PH wikidata|settlement_text}} of the Philippines|{{PH wikidata|settlement_text}}]] in the [[Philippine Province|province]] of {{PH wikidata|province}}, {{PH wikidata|country}}. According to the {{PH wikidata|population_as_of}}, it has a population of {{PH wikidata|population_total}} people.{{PH census|current}}\n\nIt is {{convert|93|km|sp=us|abbr=on|0}} South from [[Cebu City]]\n\nAlcoy is bordered to the north by the town of [[Dalaguete, Cebu|Dalaguete]], to the west is the town of [[Alegria, Cebu|Alegria]], to the east is the [[Cebu Strait]], and to the south is the town of [[Boljoon, Cebu|Boljoon]].\n\nIt is named after [[Alcoy, Spain|Alcoy]] in Spain.\n\n==Barangays==\n\nAlcoy comprises 8 barangays:\n{{PH brgy table lite|top}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202001| Atabay                         | 1754| 1535}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202002| Daan-Lungsod                   | 1863| 1569}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202003| Guiwang                        | 1564| 1490}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202004| Nug{{nbhyph}}as                | 3289| 2923}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202005| Pasol                          | 1789| 1740}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202006| Poblacion                      | 3610| 2991}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202007| [[Pugalo, Alcoy, Cebu|Pugalo]] | 2606| 2043}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|072202008| San Agustin                    |  504|  466}}\n{{PH brgy table lite|bottom|14757}}\n\n===Daan-Lungsod and Guiwang===\n\nDaan-Lungsod, formerly known as ''Mambahi''{{Citation needed|date=December 2008}}, is the southernmost barangay of Alcoy. [[Tingko Beach]] is located partly in this small barangay and partly in Guiwang. A fiesta is held in Daan-Lungsod every 3 May in honor of Santa Cruz. There is a reef called ''Mabad-on'' which appears during low tide, and is completely submerged during high tide. Mabad-on is listed as Mambahi Reef in the Philippine maritime and navigation map.{{Citation needed|date=December 2008}}\n\nThe elementary school is located in Guiwang. Guiwang celebrates 13 June the feast day of Saint Anthony of Padua.\n\nTwo ''baluwarti'' (watchtowers) still stand in the two barangays. The watchtowers are the oldest-surviving structures in Alcoy and they are reminders of the Spanish occupation of Cebu Island. They were used to warn the locals that [[Moro pirate|pirates]] were coming. Originally a settlement of Dalaguete, it was founded by the Spaniards in 1880 and was developed into a stop-over station for priests going to Dalaguete. In 1897, via a royal decree, ''Mambahi'' became a municipality and was renamed to Alcoy, after a city in Spain.<ref>https://www.beyondcebu.com/alcoy/</ref>\n\n===Poblacion===\n\nPoblacion is the principal barangay of Alcoy. It is where the main facilities of the town are located: the municipal government center, police station, and main health center.\n\n===Pugalo===\n\nThe country's largest [[Dolomite (mineral)|dolomite]] quarry is mined in [[Pugalo, Alcoy, Cebu|Pugalo]].\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Philippine Census|cols=2|align=center\n| source=[[Philippine Statistics Authority]]{{PH census|2015}}{{PH census|2010}}{{PH census|2007}}\n| name = Alcoy\n| 1903 =  6474\n| 1918 =  6575\n| 1939 =  6443\n| 1948 =  6708\n| 1960 =  7364\n| 1970 =  6965\n| 1975 =  8692\n| 1980 =  8129\n| 1990 = 10485\n| 1995 = 11539\n| 2000 = 13497\n| 2007 = 14571\n| 2010 = 14757\n| 2015 = 16979\n}}\n\n==Economy==\n\nAlcoy is mainly an agricultural town with Nug{{nbhyph}}as, a mountain barangay, more than half of commercial crops. The rest of the communities rely on subsistence fishing and backyard farming. The country's largest dolomite quarry is mined in [[Pugalo, Alcoy, Cebu|Pugalo]]. Beaches are located in Guiwang and Daanlungsod.\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Geographic location\n| Centre    = Alcoy\n| North     = [[Dalaguete, Cebu|Dalaguete]]\n| East      = ''[[Cebu Strait]]''\n| South     = [[Boljoon, Cebu|Boljoon]]\n| Southwest = [[Malabuyoc, Cebu|Malabuyoc]]\n| West      = [[Alegria, Cebu|Alegria]]\n| Northwest = [[Badian, Cebu|Badian]]\n| state     = off\n}}\n{{Cebu}}\n\n[[Category:Municipalities of Cebu]]\n", "name_user": "Uzume", "label": "safe", "comment": "defaults to the current QID", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcoy,_Cebu"}
{"title_page": "Huang Runqiu", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|image    = \n|caption = \n|office1       = [[Ministry of Ecology and Environment|Minister of Ecology and Environment]]\n|term_start1   = 29 April 2020\n|term_end1     = \n|predecessor1  = [[Li Ganjie]]\n|successor1    = \n|1blankname1   = Premier\n|1namedata1    = [[Li Keqiang]]\n|office2       = Vice-President of [[Jiusan Society]]\n|term_start2   = December 2017\n|term_end2     = \n|predecessor2  = \n|successor2    = \n|1blankname2   = President\n|1namedata2    = [[Wu Weihua]]\n|office3       = \n|term_start3   = \n|term_end3     = \n|predecessor3  = \n|successor3    = \n|name       = Huang Runqiu\n|native_name= \u9ec4\u6da6\u79cb\n|native_name_lang= zh\n|birthname  = \n|birth_date ={{birth year and age|1963|08}}\n|birth_place= [[Changsha]], [[Hunan]], China\n|death_date = <!--  {{death date and age|}} or {{death year and age| }} -->\n|death_place= \n|residence  = \n|party      = [[Jiusan Society]]\n|spouse     = <!--  {{marriage||}}  -->\n|children   = \n|parents    = \n|relations  = \n|religion   = \n|profession = \n|alma_mater = [[Chengdu University of Technology]]\n|website    = \n|signature  = \n|footnotes  =\n| module  = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes\n|s = {{linktext|\u9ec4|\u6da6|\u79cb}}\n|t = {{linktext|\u9ec3|\u6f64|\u79cb}}\n|p = Hu\u00e1ng R\u00f9nqi\u016b\n|w = \n}}\n}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Huang (surname)|Huang]]}}\n\n'''Huang Runqiu''' ({{zh|s=\u9ec4\u6da6\u79cb|p=Hu\u00e1ng R\u00f9nqi\u016b}}; born August 1963) is a Chinese politician currently serving as [[Ministry of Ecology and Environment|Minister of Ecology and Environment]].<ref>{{cite news|author1=|url=https://tech.sina.com.cn/roll/2020-04-29/doc-iircuyvi0479737.shtml |script-title=zh:\u9ec4\u6da6\u79cb\u4efb\u751f\u6001\u73af\u5883\u90e8\u90e8\u957f\uff0c\u7cfb\u6539\u9769\u5f00\u653e\u4ee5\u6765\u7b2c\u4e09\u4f4d\u62c5\u4efb\u6b63\u90e8\u957f\u7684\u975e\u4e2d\u5171\u4eba\u58eb |work=sina |date=29 April 2020 |accessdate=29 April 2020 |language=zh}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nHuang was born in [[Changsha]], [[Hunan]], in August 1963. After high school, he studied, then taught, at what is now [[Chengdu University of Technology]], becoming its vice-president and director of the State Key Laboratory of Geohazard Prevention and Geoenvironment Protection in November 2001. In December 2007, he was elected a member of the Standing Committee of the [[Jiusan Society]]. In January 2018, he was appointed vice chairman of the Sichuan Provincial Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC). In January 2014, he was appointed vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the Sichuan People's Congress, he remained in that position until March 2016, when he was transferred to Beijing and appointed vice minister of Environmental Protection.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Zhong Yuhao ({{lang|zh|\u949f\u715c\u8c6a}})|url=https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_1444203 |script-title=zh:\u73af\u4fdd\u90e8\u9886\u5bfc\u73ed\u5b50\u8c03\u6574\uff1a\u9ec4\u6da6\u79cb\u4efb\u526f\u90e8\u957f\uff0c60\u5c81\u5434\u6653\u9752\u53bb\u804c |work=thepaper.com |date=15 March 2016 |accessdate=29 April 2020 |language=zh}}</ref> On April 29, 2020, he was elevated to [[Ministry of Ecology and Environment|minister of Ecology and Environment]], replacing [[Li Ganjie]]. He concurrently serves as vice-president of Jiusan Society since December 2017.\n\nHe was a member of the 9th, 10th, 11th National Committee of the [[Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference]]. He was a delegate to the [[12th National People's Congress]]. In 2018, he was elected a member of the 13th Standing Committee of the [[Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{clear}}\n{{-}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-gov}}\n{{s-before|before=[[Li Ganjie]]}}\n{{s-title|title= [[Ministry of Ecology and Environment|Minister of Ecology and Environment]]\n|years=2020}}\n{{s-inc}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Huang, Runqiu}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Chengdu University of Technology alumni]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Changsha]]\n[[Category:Chengdu University of Technology faculty]]\n[[Category:Delegates to the 12th National People's Congress]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|image    = \n|caption = \n|office1       = [[Ministry of Ecology and Environment|Minister of Ecology and Environment]]\n|term_start1   = 29 April 2020\n|term_end1     = \n|predecessor1  = [[Li Ganjie]]\n|successor1    = \n|1blankname1   = Premier\n|1namedata1    = [[Li Keqiang]]\n|office2       = Vice-President of [[Jiusan Society]]\n|term_start2   = December 2017\n|term_end2     = \n|predecessor2  = \n|successor2    = \n|office3       = \n|term_start3   = \n|term_end3     = \n|predecessor3  = \n|successor3    = \n|name       = Huang Runqiu\n|native_name= \u9ec4\u6da6\u79cb\n|native_name_lang= zh\n|birthname  = \n|birth_date ={{birth year and age|1963|08}}\n|birth_place= [[Changsha]], [[Hunan]], China\n|death_date = <!--  {{death date and age|}} or {{death year and age| }} -->\n|death_place= \n|residence  = \n|party      = [[Jiusan Society]]\n|spouse     = <!--  {{marriage||}}  -->\n|children   = \n|parents    = \n|relations  = \n|religion   = \n|profession = \n|alma_mater = [[Chengdu University of Technology]]\n|website    = \n|signature  = \n|footnotes  =\n| module  = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes\n|s = {{linktext|\u9ec4|\u6da6|\u79cb}}\n|t = {{linktext|\u9ec3|\u6f64|\u79cb}}\n|p = Hu\u00e1ng R\u00f9nqi\u016b\n|w = \n}}\n}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Huang (surname)|Huang]]}}\n\n'''Huang Runqiu''' ({{zh|s=\u9ec4\u6da6\u79cb|p=Hu\u00e1ng R\u00f9nqi\u016b}}; born August 1963) is a Chinese politician currently serving as [[Ministry of Ecology and Environment|Minister of Ecology and Environment]].<ref>{{cite news|author1=|url=https://tech.sina.com.cn/roll/2020-04-29/doc-iircuyvi0479737.shtml |script-title=zh:\u9ec4\u6da6\u79cb\u4efb\u751f\u6001\u73af\u5883\u90e8\u90e8\u957f\uff0c\u7cfb\u6539\u9769\u5f00\u653e\u4ee5\u6765\u7b2c\u4e09\u4f4d\u62c5\u4efb\u6b63\u90e8\u957f\u7684\u975e\u4e2d\u5171\u4eba\u58eb |work=sina |date=29 April 2020 |accessdate=29 April 2020 |language=zh}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nHuang was born in [[Changsha]], [[Hunan]], in August 1963. After high school, he studied, then taught, at what is now [[Chengdu University of Technology]], becoming its vice-president and director of the State Key Laboratory of Geohazard Prevention and Geoenvironment Protection in November 2001. In December 2007, he was elected a member of the Standing Committee of the [[Jiusan Society]]. In January 2018, he was appointed vice chairman of the Sichuan Provincial Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC). In January 2014, he was appointed vice chairman of the Standing Committee of the Sichuan People's Congress, he remained in that position until March 2016, when he was transferred to Beijing and appointed vice minister of Environmental Protection.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Zhong Yuhao ({{lang|zh|\u949f\u715c\u8c6a}})|url=https://www.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_1444203 |script-title=zh:\u73af\u4fdd\u90e8\u9886\u5bfc\u73ed\u5b50\u8c03\u6574\uff1a\u9ec4\u6da6\u79cb\u4efb\u526f\u90e8\u957f\uff0c60\u5c81\u5434\u6653\u9752\u53bb\u804c |work=thepaper.com |date=15 March 2016 |accessdate=29 April 2020 |language=zh}}</ref> On April 29, 2020, he was elevated to [[Ministry of Ecology and Environment|minister of Ecology and Environment]], replacing [[Li Ganjie]]. He concurrently serves as vice-president of Jiusan Society since December 2017.\n\nHe was a member of the 9th, 10th, 11th National Committee of the [[Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference]]. He was a delegate to the [[12th National People's Congress]]. In 2018, he was elected a member of the 13th Standing Committee of the [[Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{clear}}\n{{-}}\n{{s-sta